      "content": "i get that, but it feels like the \"economic disruption\" argument is just being used as an excuse by big coal to keep things the same. like, at what point do we stop treating old industries as if they are just as important as the technologies that actually work for the climate? shouldn't the focus just be on the fact that coal is becoming obsolete?",
